#: templates/faq.html:3 templates/main.html:7 templates/main.html:19
#: templates/toc.html:12
msgid "About route.lw1.at"
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:5
msgid "What is route.lw1.at?"
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:7
msgid ""
"This is a website/tool that allows you to find the best way to travel in "
"Austria, with a special focus on public transport. You can think of it as"
" a mix between ÖBB Scotty, Wien Mobil, Google Maps and OsmAnd."
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:15
msgid ""
"What can I do here that ÖBB/Scotty/Wien Mobil apps can't do? Why should I"
" not use route.lw1.at?"
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:18
msgid ""
"While most results should be pretty similar to what you get from ÖBB apps"
" (after all, it uses the same schedule), there are a few additional "
"features that are not easily possible on other platforms:"
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:25
msgid ""
"Combining multiple datasets: I strive to import every available schedule "
"in Austria so that routing can combine many different types of public "
"transport."
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:32
msgid ""
"Schedule on a map: The map shows the current scheduled position (see <a "
"href=\"#realtime\">realtime</a>) of all public transport. This gives an "
"intuitive insight into the state of public transport in different regions"
" and at different times."
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:40
msgid ""
"Open Source and Open Data: The full source code of the website and all "
"data I am using and that I have added is available under free licenses. "
"Therefore, others can build on top of this."
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:47
msgid ""
"Fast: Even complex searches should finish quite a bit faster than in "
"other apps."
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:52
msgid ""
"Isochrones: You can find out how far one can travel from a certain "
"position within a specified time. Which places are hard to reach by "
"public transport?"
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:58
msgid ""
"Indoor routing: As all connections are routed using OpenStreetMap data, "
"if public transport stations are mapped correctly, you can see the exact "
"path you need to take inside."
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:64
msgid ""
"More realistic transfer times: The time it takes to walk from one "
"platform to another is based on the actual path walked."
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:70
msgid ""
"Minimal: While some public transport apps can be slow with unreliable "
"internet connections, I also have <a "
"href=\"https://lite.route.lw1.at/\">a lite version</a> that should load "
"even with the slowest possible connection."
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:77
msgid ""
"Wiener Linien Realtime Warnings: While there is no real support for "
"realtime data, I do integrate the realtime notices from Wiener Linien "
"into the output. See below for <a href=\"#wl-rt\">more information on the"
" GTFS RT proxy</a>."
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:84
msgid ""
"Austria-focused: As I only focus on public transport inside Austria, I "
"can run experiments and provide fast results that would be much harder to"
" achieve if I had to consider global datasets."
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:90
msgid "Of course, this comes with a few tradeoffs and disadvantages:"
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:96
msgid ""
"No realtime data: For now every result assumes the pre-published "
"schedules are correct. <a href=\"#realtime\">See below</a> for more about"
" realtime data."
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:102
msgid ""
"No guarantees: At the end of the day, this is a hobby project, so I "
"cannot give any guarantees or promises about the accuracy and reliability"
" of the website and data. However, I promise that all code and datasets I"
" create will continue to be published under free licenses, so that they "
"can be integrated and improved by others."
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:111
msgid ""
"No extensive documentation: I use this project to experiment with some "
"ideas I have, which means that I don't always find time to properly "
"document everything. I will try to keep this page updated with the most "
"important information."
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:120
msgid ""
"Minimal resources: This is just a hobby project and I only work on it "
"when it's fun, so some ideas are just not feasible for me to solve "
"myself. Therefore, this project primarily builds on top of the amazing "
"work by others, merging it into one website both to present it as a "
"useful tool and as a celebration of Open Data and Open Source."
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:128
msgid ""
"Austria-focused: As I ignore all data from outside of Austria, "
"route.lw1.at is obviously useless if you want to travel somewhere else. "
"So use <a href=\"#transitous\">Transitous</a> if you are not in Austria."
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:135
msgid "What is MOTIS?"
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:137
msgid ""
"<a href=\"https://github.com/motis-project/motis\">MOTIS</a> is the main "
"software powering route.lw1.at."
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:142
msgid ""
"Essentially, route.lw1.at is a hosted instance of the MOTIS software with"
" Austrian public transport data and a few extensions added by me."
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:148
msgid "Are there any modifications to MOTIS on route.lw1.at?"
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:149
msgid ""
"I try to contribute all fixes I make to the MOTIS source code back to the"
" original project."
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:153
msgid ""
"On top of this, I also make some minor changes to the web UI. I try to "
"keep this list of changes up-to-date:"
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:159
msgid ""
"The live positions on the map default to showing the color instead of the"
" realtime status (due to the lack of realtime data)."
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:165
msgid ""
"'Use routed transfers' is enabled by default (as I am able to always "
"calculate the data necessary on import)."
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:171
msgid ""
"The hillshading tiles are loaded from maps.lw1.at which forwards the "
"original images. Therefore visitor data is not sent to any third-party "
"servers."
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:177
msgid ""
"The server code is compiled with some different optimizations as it only "
"needs to run on my server."
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:183
msgid "You can find the list of all changes on top of MOTIS here:"
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:191
msgid "What is Transitous?"
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:195
msgid ""
"is a community-run provider-neutral international public transport "
"routing service."
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:200
msgid "from"
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:203
msgid ""
"route.lw1.at is heavily inspired by Transitous and aims to be a smaller, "
"Austria-focused version of it that can experiment and update more easily "
"and frequently, due to not having to handle the size of global datasets."
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:210
msgid "Is this website finished?"
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:212
msgid ""
"route.lw1.at is more or less a permanent work-in-progress, as it is a "
"hobby project. That said, it is already very useful, and I use it most of"
" the time when trying to get to a place I have not been before."
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:218
msgid "Who is behind this website?"
msgstr ""

#: templates/faq.html:220
msgid ""
"I am Lukas Winkler and I currently work primarily on my PhD in "
"Astrophysics. But I try to find time to work on fun side-projects in my "
"free time. Since I live in Vienna and use public transport a lot, this "
"seemed like an interesting topic to explore. Also, I recently realized "
"that I have some unused space on my server, so I thought I could this "
"platform for others to use too."
msgstr ""

